<p>I already have this code to match if any numbers in a list match any numbers in the other list. However, I need to modify my recursion so it returns false if the same number is found in the same position on both lists.</p>  <p>For example:</p>  <p><code>[5,3,4,6,2]</code> is compatible with <code>[3,1,2,2,7]</code>; and <code>[1,3,4,9,2]</code> is incompatible with <code>[4,5,2,9,8]</code> because both lists have a 9 in the 4th position.</p>  <p>Here is the code I have so far:</p>  <pre><code>common_elements([], L) :-     fail. common_elements([H|T], L) :-     memberchk(H, L), !. common_elements([H|T], L) :-     common_elements(T, L). </code></pre>  <p>SWI-Prolog example inputs and outputs for current code:</p>  <pre><code>?- common_elements([1,2,3,4],[6,7,8,9]). false.  ?- common_elements([1,2,3,6],[6,7,8,9]). true. </code></pre>